==English==

===Etymology===
From {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[θρόνος]]}}''' (thronos) “chair”, “throne”

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/θrəʊn/}}
*{{audio|en-us-throne.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{rhymes|əʊn}}

====Homophones====
*[[thrown]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[ornate]] seat a [[King]] or [[Queen]] sits on for formal occasions, usually placed on a raised [[dais]] in the [[throne room]].
#* ''He approached the '''throne''' reverently.''
# {{colloquial}} The [[lavatory]] or [[toilet]].
#* ''She’s on the '''throne'''.''
# {{context|Biblical tradition}} The third highest order of [[angel]] in Christian [[angelology]], ranked above [[minion]]s and below [[cherub]]im.
# {{context|music}} A type of [[stool]] used by [[drummer]]s.

